# AutoDown Comprehensive Example

This document demonstrates _various_ **formatting** features.

## Text Formatting

AutoDown supports **bold text**, _italic text_, and `inline code`.

You can also create [links](https://example.com) and embed images:

![AutoDown Logo](https://example.com/logo.png)

## Lists

### Unordered Lists

- First item with **bold**
- Second item with _italic_
- Third item with `code`

### Ordered Lists

1. Step one
2. Step two
3. Step three

## Code Blocks

```rust
fn main() {
    println!("Hello, AutoDown!");
}
```

## Math

Inline math: %{ E = mc^2 }

Block math:

%{
    sum(i=0..n, f(i)) = integral_0^infinity f(x) dx
%}

## Blockquotes

> This is a blockquote.
> It can contain multiple lines.

---

## Advanced Features

### Conditional Content

$if show_advanced {
This content only appears when show_advanced is true.
$else {
This is the default content.
}

### Loop Content

$for item in items {
- Item: ${item}
}

### Component Call

$Card(title: "Example", width: 100) {
This is the card content with ${variable} interpolation.
}

## Table Example

| Name | Type | Description |
|------|------|-------------|
| id | int | Unique identifier |
| name | str | Display name |
| active | bool | Active status |

---

Thank you for reading!
